9. AUTH - Forgot / Reset Password
================================================================================
Files: public/forgot-password.php, public/reset-password.php

FORGOT PASSWORD WORKFLOW:
1. User enters email
2. POST with CSRF token
3. Server: site_request_password_reset(email)
   a. Rate limit: 10 attempts per 48 hours
   b. If exceeded: locks account (requires admin unlock)
   c. Generates random token
   d. Stores SHA256 hash in password_reset_tokens table
   e. Token expires in 30 minutes
   f. Sends email with reset link
4. Shows generic message (prevents email enumeration):
   "If that email is associated with an account, you will receive a reset link shortly."

RESET PASSWORD WORKFLOW:
1. User clicks link: /reset-password.php?token={rawToken}
2. On load: site_validate_reset_token(rawToken)
   a. SHA256 hash lookup in password_reset_tokens
   b. Check expiry (30 min)
   c. Check not already used
3. If valid: show new password form
4. User enters new password + confirmation
5. POST with CSRF token
6. Server: site_apply_password_reset(rawToken, newPassword)
   a. Re-validates token
   b. Updates user password hash
   c. Invalidates ALL tokens for this user
   d. Redirect to login with success message

