39. BACKEND - Authentication & Security
================================================================================
Files: src/auth.php (admin), src/site_auth.php (customer)

TWO AUTH SYSTEMS:
1. Admin auth (opd_* functions): session key 'opd_user', roles: admin/manager
2. Customer auth (site_* functions): session key 'site_user', roles: customer/vendor

SESSION SECURITY:
- HttpOnly cookies
- Secure flag (HTTPS detection)
- Strict SameSite policy
- Session regeneration on login

CSRF PROTECTION:
- Token stored in session
- Validated via X-CSRF-TOKEN header or _csrf POST field
- Required on all state-changing requests

RATE LIMITING:
- Admin login: tracked per email
- Customer login: tracked per email
- Password reset: 10 attempts per 48 hours
- Exceeding limit: account locked (requires admin unlock)
- Stored in rate_limit table

PASSWORD SECURITY:
- Hashed with PASSWORD_DEFAULT (bcrypt)
- Timing-safe comparison (hash_equals)
- Dummy hash for non-existent users (prevents timing attacks)
- Reset tokens: SHA256 hashed, 30-min expiry, single-use

ID GENERATION:
- opd_generate_id(prefix): prefix-{32 hex chars} (128-bit random)

